Let \(f:\mathbf{R}\to\mathbf{R}\) satisfy \(f(\cot x)=\cos 2x+\sin 2x\) for all \(0 < x<\pi\). Also, let \(g(x)=f(x)f(1 - x)\), where \(x\in[- 1,1]\). Find the maximum and minimum values of \(g(x)\).

Proof: Since \(f(\cot x)=\frac{1-\tan^{2}x + 2\tan x}{1+\tan^{2}x}\), let \(t = \cot x\), then \(f(t)=\frac{t^{2}+2t - 1}{t^{2}+1}\).

So, \(g(x)=\frac{x^{2}+2x - 1}{x^{2}+1}\cdot\frac{(1 - x)^{2}+2(1 - x)-1}{(1 - x)^{2}+1}\)
\[
=\frac{(x^{2}-x)^{2}-8(x^{2}-x)-2}{(x^{2}-x)^{2}+2(x^{2}-x)+2}
\]

Let \(x^{2}-x = u\), \(x\in[-1,1]\), then \(u\in\left[-\frac{1}{4},2\right]\). Thus
\[
g(u)=\frac{u^{2}-8u - 2}{u^{2}+2u + 2}=1-\frac{10u + 4}{u^{2}+2u + 2}=1-2\cdot\frac{5u + 2}{u^{2}+2u + 2}
\]

Let \(5u+2 = s\), \(s\in\left[\frac{3}{4},12\right]\), then \(u=\frac{s - 2}{5}\). So
\[
\begin{gathered}
u^{2}+2u + 2=\frac{1}{25}(s^{2}+6s + 34)\\
\frac{5u + 2}{u^{2}+2u + 2}=\frac{25s}{s^{2}+6s + 34}=\frac{25}{s+\frac{34}{s}+6}
\end{gathered}
\]

By the monotonicity of the Nike function, we know that \(\frac{553}{12}\geqslant s+\frac{34}{s}\geqslant2\sqrt{34}\), and the equal signs are taken when \(s = \sqrt{34}\) and \(s=\frac{3}{4}\) respectively.

So
\[
\begin{gathered}
g_{\min}=1-2\times\frac{25}{2\sqrt{34}+6}=4-\sqrt{34}\\
g_{\max}=1-2\times\frac{25}{\frac{553}{12}+6}=\frac{1}{25}
\end{gathered}
\]

